 oder von The Walking Dead - untersucht. Andererseits illustrieren die popkulturellen Welten wie beispielsweise von Game of Thrones oder der Harry-Potter-Reihe wissenschafts- und gendertheoretische Ansätze.  aUnderstanding pop culture with the help of science - illustrating science with pop culture.  afunded by Geistes- und Kulturwissenschaftliches Promotionskolleg des Fachbereich 02 (GeKKo) der Universität Kassel  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aFilm. 4aGedankenexperimente. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aLinguistik. 4aLiteratur. 4aMedien. 4aPhilosophie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aFilm.  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aLinguistics.  aLiterature.  aMedia.  aPhilosophy.  aThought Experiments.1 aBachmann, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBodden, Tamara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöhnert, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöhnert, Martin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFuhlmann, Madeline Isabelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGens, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKapitz, Lisa Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarthäuser, Vanessa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReh, Jannis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReszke, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReszke, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRiechert, Nadja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScharf, Oliver, econtributor.